      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MATERIAL MADAM (5) has been narrowly beaten both starts this preparation and has been kept on the fresh side. Has the rails gate and keeps the handy 1.5kg claim. Is still shy of her best numbers and is proven third up. STREET DIVA (1) won this grade three back and has been within range in stronger races since. Benefits from the 1.5kg, and is a decent chance to bounce back. STARDARMUS (2) resumes and has won fresh. Has a good record this course/distance and can make the finish if presented on song. RARE ORO (10) resumed in good order but was plain here following. Fitter and has a 2kg claim today. Keep onside. EASTCOAST MISS (3) presents off better grade on the synthetic with a 2kg claimer aboard. She's hard to catch, but her best form would see her in the money.",
